26/02/2004
MOSTAR, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Prime Minister Adnan Terzic met on Wednesday (25 February) with his Croatian counterpart, Ivo Sanader, who assured him that his country would help BiH in efforts to sign a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU. 
Noting their joint history, Sanader said the countries would share their future in the Union.
In other news, the Croatian government is proposing an urgent parliamentary procedure to pass amendments to the pension insurance law. 
Sanader says the changes will raise average pensions by more than 6 per cent. 
(Vjesnik, Vecernji List - 26/02/04; HINA, HRT - 25/02/04)
